import numpy as np

import csv
f = open("DeviceMotion.csv", "rt",encoding="utf8")
reader = csv.reader(f)
h = next(reader)
print("Features of Device Motion Sensor which we use:")
print("*(0,1,2) Attitude : ", h[2:5])
print("*(3,4,5) Gravity : ", h[5:8])
print("*(6,7,8) Rotation : ", h[12:15])
print("*(9,10,11) Acceleration :", h[15:18])

print("\nConsider data subject # 3 (after cleaning data):")
series = np.genfromtxt("sub_3.csv", delimiter = ",")
print("shape of time-series : ", series.shape, "[the last column is label]\n")
print("For example: row 2017 to row 2021 data")
print(series[2017:2021,:])

*(9,10,11) Acceleration : ['userAcceleration.x', 'userAcceleration.y', 'userAcceleration.z']

import pandas as pd
from pandas import Series
import matplotlib.pylab as plt
import matplotlib.pyplot as pyplt
print("*** Acceleration Data:")
acr = pd.DataFrame(series[::50,9:12])
lbl = pd.DataFrame(series[::50,12])
acr.plot()
plt.xlabel('Second', fontsize=18)
plt.ylabel('Normalised Value', fontsize=16)
lgnd=plt.legend()
lgnd.get_texts()[0].set_text('x')
lgnd.get_texts()[1].set_text('y')
lgnd.get_texts()[2].set_text('z')
fig = pyplt.gcf()
fig.set_size_inches(18, 8)
plt.show()

print("*** And Corresponding Labels:")
print("*** The below graph shows point-by-point labels for above graph")
lbl.plot(style='k.' , legend=False)
plt.yticks([0,1,2,3,4,5,6], labels, rotation=45)
plt.xlabel('Second', fontsize=18)
fig = pyplt.gcf()
fig.set_size_inches(18, 8)
plt.show()

In [87]:
ts = pd.DataFrame(series)
groups = ts.groupby(12, axis=0)
labels = pd.DataFrame()
labels = ['null', 'Down to Stairs', 'Up to Stairs', 'Sit', 'Stand', 'Walk', 'Jog']
for name, group in groups:
    print("*** All 12 Features For Label <<", labels[int(name)], ">>")
    tmp = group.values
    tmp = pd.DataFrame(tmp[::50])
    tmp.plot()
    plt.xlabel('Second', fontsize=18)
    plt.ylabel('Normalised Value', fontsize=16)
    fig = pyplt.gcf()
    fig.set_size_inches(18, 8)
    plt.show()
